##  Reproducing Results

### Prerequisites
```bash
# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # or: source new_vast/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128
pip install transformers accelerate datasets
pip install scikit-learn pandas numpy
pip install matplotlib seaborn scipy
```
## Quick Start

### Prerequisites: Create and Activate Virtual Environment
```bash
# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv new_vast

# Activate virtual environment
source new_vast/bin/activate

# Install requirements
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 1: Pretraining (Optional - checkpoints included)

If you want to retrain the models from scratch (takes ~2-3 hours on 8× B200 GPUs):
# RoBERTa-base
accelerate launch --multi_gpu --num_processes 8 training_new.py --preset roberta-base --train-epochs 5 --per-device-train-batch-size 8 --gradient-accumulation-steps 1 --max-length 512 --early-stop-patience 0 --save-total-limit 3 --overwrite-run-dir

# DeBERTa-v3-large
accelerate launch --multi_gpu --num_processes 8 training_new.py --preset deberta-v3-large --train-epochs 5 --per-device-train-batch-size 4 --gradient-accumulation-steps 1 --max-length 512 --early-stop-patience 0 --save-total-limit 3 --overwrite-run-dir

# ModernBERT-large
accelerate launch --multi_gpu --num_processes 8 training_new.py --preset modernbert-large --train-epochs 5 --per-device-train-batch-size 4 --gradient-accumulation-steps 1 --max-length 512 --early-stop-patience 0 --save-total-limit 3 --overwrite-run-dir
```

**Note:** Pretrained checkpoints are already included in `runs/*/best/` directories.

### Step 2: Fine-tuning Experiments

Run all 30 experiments automatically (~3 hours on 8× B200 GPUs):
# Make script executable
chmod +x run_experiments.sh

# Run all experiments (3 models × 30 runs = 90 total experiments)
./run_experiments.sh
```

This will:
- Fine-tune RoBERTa-base 30 times (seeds 42-71)
- Fine-tune DeBERTa-v3-large 30 times (seeds 42-71)
- Fine-tune ModernBERT-large 30 times (seeds 42-71)
- Save results to `results_30runs/` directory

### Step 3: Analysis

Generate statistics and visualizations:
python analyze.py

This creates:
- `summary_statistics.csv` - Mean, std, min, max F1 scores
- `statistical_tests.csv` - p-values and t-test results
- `f1_boxplot.png` - Box plot comparison
- `f1_barplot.png` - Bar plot with error bars
- `f1_violin.png` - Violin plot
- `training_time.png` - Training time comparison
- `loss_comparison.png` - Train/val loss comparison
- `radar_plot.png` - Overall model comparison
- `radar_plot_per_class.png` - Per-class F1 comparison

### Step 4: View Results

# View summary statistics
cat results_30runs/summary_statistics.csv

# View statistical tests
cat results_30runs/statistical_tests.csv

# List all visualizations
ls results_30runs/*.png


